title: Doubly Robust Estimation of Survival Differences with Censored Data
text: basic example shows solve common problem: methods blanche_survdiff pseudo_survdiff.
code: library(drsurv) #> Loading required package: survival ## basic example code  df <- rotterdam df$time <- pmin(df$rtime, df$dtime) / 365.25 df$status <- ifelse(df$recur == 1 | df$death == 1, 1, 0) df$censor <- 1 - df$status drFit.sjovan <-  sjovan_survdiff(    oformula = Surv(time, status) ~ chemo + year + age + meno +      size + factor(grade) + nodes + pgr + er + hormon,    ofunc = "survreg",    cformula = Surv(time, censor) ~ chemo + year + age,    cfunc = "survreg",    eformula = chemo ~ year + age + meno + size +      factor(grade) + nodes + pgr + er + hormon,    method = "DR",    times = c(2.5, 5, 7.5),    se.type = "sandwich",    data = df  ) drFit.sjovan #> $est.S1 #> [1] 0.7661741 0.6032550 0.5224925 #>  #> $se.S1 #> [1] 0.03440273 0.02906199 0.14520126 #>  #> $est.S0 #> [1] 0.7190130 0.5515392 0.4670844 #>  #> $se.S0 #> [1] 0.07008758 0.07427899 0.10500988 #>  #> $est.diff #> [1] 0.04716109 0.05171581 0.05540801 #>  #> $se.diff #> [1] 0.06863352 0.07611256 0.14153032

Let estimated inverse probability censoring weights $$\hat{U}_i(t) =  \frac{I_{\tilde{T_i} \leq t} \Delta_i}{\hat{G}_c(\tilde{T}_i, X_i,  \boldsymbol{Z}_i)} + \frac{I_{\tilde{T_i}> t}}{\hat{G}_c(t, X_i,  \boldsymbol{Z}_i)}.$$ let \(\hat{\beta}^\dagger, \hat{\boldsymbol{\gamma}}^\dagger\) denote parameter estimates resulting inverse probability censoring weighted, propensity score unweighted, score equations logistic model estimated via maximum likelihood among subset individuals either event time t remained observation least time t. doubly robust estimator causal event probability (one minus survival) exposure level \(x = 1\) $$\frac{1}{n}\sum_{= 1}^n  W(1, \boldsymbol{Z}_i; \hat{\boldsymbol{\alpha}})\hat{U}_i(t)\left(I_{T_i \leq  t} - Q_k(1, \boldsymbol{Z}_i, \hat{\beta}^\dagger, \hat{\boldsymbol{\gamma}}^\dagger)\right) + \frac{1}{n}\sum_{= 1}^n Q_k(1, \boldsymbol{Z}_i, \hat{\beta}^\dagger, \hat{\boldsymbol{\gamma}}^\dagger), $$ term \(I_{T_i \leq t}\) defined 0 individuals censored time \(t\), otherwise fully observed. text: presented Wang 2018, let jackknife pseudo observation $$th subject $$\hat{S}^(t) = n \hat{S}(t) - (n - 1)\hat{S}^{-}(t),$$ \(\hat{S}(t)\) estimator survival probability time \(t\) using \(n\) subjects, \(\hat{S}^{-}(t)\) estimator survival probability time \(t\) leaving \(\)th subject estimation procedure. assumption censoring implied way pseudo observations computed, .e., inverse probability censoring weighted estimators censoring distribution may depend covariates, nonparametric estimators stratified covariates, simply Kaplan-Meier estimators censoring assumed independent covariates. use working outcome model conditional survival probability: $$\log[-\log\{v_i(X_i)\}]=\log[-\log\{p(T > t | X_i, \boldsymbol{Z}_i)\}] = \beta^\star X_i+h(X_i,\boldsymbol{Z}_i;\boldsymbol{\gamma}^\star),$$ \(\log(-\log(x))\) link function coincides proportional hazards model fits survival time point. note , unlike Cox model, estimator assume anything survival function prior time point \(t\). parameters model estimated solving generalized estimating equations \(\hat{S}^(t)\) used outcome variable. Let \(\hat{v}_i(x) = \exp[-\exp\{\hat{\beta}^\star x+h(x,\boldsymbol{Z}_i;\hat{\boldsymbol{\gamma}}^\star)\}]\). logistic regression model propensity exposure assumed estimated. doubly robust estimator difference survival probability time \(t\) $$\frac{1}{n}\sum_{= 1}^n\left[ \frac{X_i \hat{S}^(t) - (X_i - g(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \hat{\boldsymbol{\alpha}}))\hat{v}_i(1)}{g(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \hat{\boldsymbol{\alpha}})} - \frac{(1 - X_i) \hat{S}^(t) + (X_i - g(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \hat{\boldsymbol{\alpha}}))\hat{v}_i(0)}{1 - g(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \hat{\boldsymbol{\alpha}})}\right].$$ Although Wang proposed variance estimator, found biased upward, suggest instead using bootstrap variance estimation. Thus, implement bootstrap variance estimator.

title: Estimate the survival curves in two treatment groups — sjovan_survdiff
text: Following Bai et al. 2013 Sjölander Vansteelandt 2017, consider following estimating equation \(S_x(t) = p\{T(x) > t\}\): $$\sum_{= 1}^n \left[S_x(t) - \frac{I_{X_i = x} I_{\tilde{T}_i > t}}{\bar{g}(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \boldsymbol{\alpha})G_c(t, X_i, \boldsymbol{Z}_i)} - \frac{I_{X_i = x} - \bar{g}(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \boldsymbol{\alpha})}{\bar{g}(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \boldsymbol{\alpha})} H(t, \boldsymbol{Z}_i, X = x) - \right. \\ \left. \frac{I_{X_i = x} - \bar{g}(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \boldsymbol{\alpha})}{\bar{g}(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \boldsymbol{\alpha})} H(t, \boldsymbol{Z}_i, X = x) \int_0^t\frac{d\, M_c(u, \boldsymbol{Z}_i, X_i, \tilde{T}_i, \Delta_i)}{G_c(u, X_i, \boldsymbol{Z}_i)H(u, \boldsymbol{Z}_i, X_i)}\right] = 0, $$ \(\bar{g}(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \boldsymbol{\alpha}) = g(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \boldsymbol{\alpha})^x (1 - g(\boldsymbol{Z}_i, \boldsymbol{\alpha}))^{(1-x)}\), \(H(t, \boldsymbol{Z}, X)\) model \(p\{T > t | \boldsymbol{Z}, X\}\), \(M_c(t, \boldsymbol{Z}, X, \tilde{T}, \Delta)\) martingale increment censoring distribution. unbiased estimating equation \(S_x(t)\) either \(H(t, \boldsymbol{Z}, X)\) correctly specified censoring confounding, .e., correctly specified model \(p\{T(x) > t | \boldsymbol{Z}, X\}\) \(G_c(u, X, \boldsymbol{Z})\) \(g(\boldsymbol{Z}, \boldsymbol{\alpha})\) correctly specified censoring confounding, respectively. obtain estimates difference survival probabilities, one must specify models unknown functions \(g\), \(G_c\), \(H\), get estimates , plug estimating equations, solve \(S_x(t)\) \(x \\{0, 1\}\). package, one can use semiparametric Cox models parametric survival models outcome censoring distributions, logistic regression propensity score model. Bai et al. 2013 provide expression variance estimator accounts uncertainty due estimation propensity score \(g\) censoring distribution \(G_c\).
